cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a learning framework for training a powerful classifier through a fusion module that combines feature maps generated from parallel neural networks. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as image classification and performs experiments on datasets such as CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and ImageNet. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of online-knowledge distillation, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks and the fusion of features also falls under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
